{"questionId":"27907","questionHtml":"<p>Write down suitable hypotheses for this test.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> be the probability of a student choosing healthy options)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mi>p</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0A1</strong> </em>for correct hypotheses with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> in place of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>. Accept equivalent hypotheses in words.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27907","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.16a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down suitable hypotheses for this test.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}